{
  "texts": [
    "Here, the Stockwell transformation was performed to partition the frequency bands, then the feature vectors were calculated with respect to the amplitude distribution.",
    "Based on these features, the most optimal feature values were selected using kPCA, and the k-nearest neighbor classification technique was employed to categorize the signals as Healthy, Interictal, and Ictal.",
    "Moreover, it obtained the advantages of reduced time complexity and increased classification accuracy.",
    "Atal et al.",
    "22 developed an automatic classification system for discovering the abnormalities of the input EEG signals."
  ]
}